    "transcriptLines": [["00:00","00:02","Section 2."],["00:02","00:07","You will hear a guide talking to a group of visitors in a garden."],["00:07","00:12","First, you'll have some time to look at questions 11-14."],["00:31","00:37","Now, listen carefully and answer questions 11-14."],["00:37","00:47","Hello, welcome to Pine Garden. My name is Manuel and I'd like to tell you a few things about our establishment before you all wander off and begin your exploration of the grounds."],["00:47","00:51","I know you're keen to begin, so I'll try to keep this short."],["00:51","00:55","First of all, I'd like to explain what you can do with your ticket."],["00:55","00:59","If you want to be closer to nature, you could visit our planting area."],["00:59","01:03","In that area, visitors can plant small flowers and bulbs that will grow and become part of the garden."],["01:03","01:09","The planting activity is completely free."],["01:09","01:12","However, if you have sensitive hands, you'll need to purchase garden gloves to protect your skin."],["01:12","01:18","Here at Pine Garden, we sell a number of wooden goods, card from trees that have been felt in our very own pine forest."],["01:18","01:24","If you feel like getting involved and having a go yourself, you can join one of our <span class='answer-highlight'>bush timbering lessons</span>, free of charge, where you'll be able to make your own kearing under the supervision of a skilled craftsman."],["01:24","01:37","The most popular attraction in the garden is our aviary, where you can observe a whole range of bird species."],["01:37","01:44","Entry to this section is free, but you have to pay a small supplement in order to enter the hummingbird section."],["01:44","01:50","Also, the insect hut not far from it may arouse your interest, there you can find some interesting insects such as butterflies, <span class='answer-highlight'>pocket ladybugs</span>, dragonflies, and so on."],["01:50","02:00","And there's no extra charge for that."],["02:00","02:03","Unfortunately, there are some areas that are temporarily off limits to visitors today."],["02:03","02:08","For example, the gift shop that closed earlier this year and won't be open for another month or so."],["02:08","02:14","As I mentioned before, however, you're free to visit our restaurant for food and snacks, and if you're looking to purchase a gift, why not buy that special someone a potted bush or orchid from our <span class='answer-highlight'>plant care centre</span>."],["02:15","02:27","And our new treetop cafe is under construction, which will be very impressive when it's finished."],["02:27","02:33","In fact, the <span class='answer-highlight'>model town</span> is already open ahead of schedule, and it's attracting a lot of people."],["02:33","02:38","Now, our tourist office is normally available to provide tourists with a variety of help. However, the officer is sick at home today."],["02:38","02:46","Please do not let this discourage you from visiting these as they provide quite an experience."],["02:46","02:52","Before you hear the rest of the talk, you'll have some time to look at questions 15 to 20."],["02:54","03:01","Now listen and answer questions 15 to 20."],["03:08","03:18","I also would like to introduce you to our plant specialists who are responsible for the wonderful plant displays here at Pine Garden."],["03:38","03:46","Mrs Mary is one of our experts, and she is personally responsible for our beautiful display of <span class='answer-highlight'>plants that are all found growing naturally in the local area</span>."],["03:46","03:55","Mr. Berson has the difficult task of growing <span class='answer-highlight'>varieties of plants that are suited to much drier and hotter climates</span> than ours, which means we do not have to store water on site."],["03:55","04:06","If you visit the glass house, you'll be able to see many plants that he has managed to cultivate without the need for rain or irrigation."],["04:06","04:15","Mr. Smith is responsible for the <span class='answer-highlight'>produce that you can eat in our restaurant</span>, which ranges from varieties that grow under the ground to those that grow on trees and bushes."],["04:15","04:25","Now Mr. Noony here is our expert on the most commonly growing plant in the world, Grass."],["04:26","04:33","You may have noticed how <span class='answer-highlight'>beautifully green and lush our grounds</span> are thanks to his specialist knowledge."],["04:33","04:39","Mr. Scanlan ensures that our <span class='answer-highlight'>soil is full of nutrients</span> so that the natural habitat is supported and encouraged."],["04:39","04:47","He does this by fertilising the earth with a special formula of his own creation."],["04:47","04:53","Finally, I would like to introduce you all to Dr. Mandelson."],["04:53","04:57","He is the manager of our landscaping team and works closely with our other experts to <span class='answer-highlight'>ensure that everyone works together to create a landscape that is both beautiful and sustainable</span>."],["04:57","05:09","Well, that just about rounds it up. Now if anyone has any questions?"],["05:09","05:16","That is the end of section 2. You now have half a minute to check your answers."]],
